<br>
Freegle seems somewhat confused, for seasons he has been an assistant, a healer to many courageous adventures. He has aways enjoyed the protection of the Strong Shield arm of many friends. <br>
<br>
Why now all of a sudden a spirit needs Freegle to be a hero, rather than a simple baker. Was his shamantic service and baking not enough to fullfill the spirits desires and needs?<br>
<br>
Freegle afraid and uncertain of how to become a hero, begins to travel, to begin to ask people what he needs or not needs to be hero. He first travels to the Burning Woods on the Continent of Kunark to search for a hero to ask a question or two.<br>
